London-based designer Crispin Sinclair is seeking £50,000 of funding on site Indiegogo . 
  Called the Babel Bike it has a host of features including a roll cage . 
  The bike also has foot protectors and an electric motor  . 
  The Babel Bike was designed by London-based Cris pin Sinclair - son of the famous British inventor Sir Clive Sinclair . 
  It has front and rear lights, rear view mirrors and even a car horn . 
  And the roll cage keeps the cyclist safe against trucks and buses turning into them . 
  The electric bike will cost £2,499 ($3,693) in the UK and £3,499 in the US . 
 